{
  "texts": [
    "Upon inspecting the rules, we found rules that might confuse the model in each of these three instances: (1) \"Doesn't Contribute Meaningfully\" and \"No Neutral/Transgender/Harm a specific person/Promo/Meta\", (2) \"No Rude/Hostile Comment\", and (3) \"No Delta Abuse/Misuse or Should Award Delta\".",
    "We find that 13.7% of the FP comments (10/73) contained links, and while all three SLMs got these incorrectly, at least one LLM got each of these 10 moderation outcomes right.",
    "Similarly for comments tagging and replying to the previous comment, we find that LLMs correctly identify 51% (36/73) comments as non-violating.",
    "On the other hand, for comments mentioning delta we actually found that there were some com- ments in the training set nearly identical to the examples that the SLMs moderated (e.g., \"∆\", \"!delta rip\", \"Then delta this mannn\") which were removed by human moderators.",
    "Further, the rule \"No Delta Abuse/Misuse or Should Award Delta\" is a clear dismissal of these kind of comments."
  ]
}